lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Part of Patch Message: September 26 2002 3:00am</span><hr size=1> Hmm..<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong my fellow warriors.  I am not complaining but am concerned about the current situation.<br>
<br>
I have played nothing but a warrior since day 1 in these lands.  Yes, my main duty, was to play a tank in the old days but times have changed.<br>
<br>
I have to be honest.  I got tired of the old keeping up with the tanks hp and ac game and changed it to what I wanted now and what I perceived as fun.  Why was this?  And yes I put up with a lot of ribbing in my own guild from my fellow warriors for going with offensive skills in AA first instead of DEF.  But they aren't ribbing me anymore.  Will I ever go after the def skills?  Sure as soon as they are fixed properly.  According to my testing the freaking offensive aa skills work a lot better than the def AA skills.<br>
<br>
To be honest I would consider myself lucky to reach 6000hp..right now am about 5600 but can I still tank mobs?  Heck yes.  Sure can.  Okay maybe I won't last as long as someone with 7000hp but I can play a tank and a damage giver.<br>
<br>
Simple...look at the skills we have in AA and look at what we had when the world started out.  Huge difference yes?  Granted some of our AA skills don't work as they should but someday they will.<br>
<br>
I can do 20k+ damage on a major mob like Tunare.  If someone told me I could do that much damage against one mob when I first started out as a warrior I would have laughed right in their faces.<br>
<br>
But as I have stated times are a changing.  We can solo now..well at least at some places in luclin.  But soloing is boring as all hell!<br>
<br>
We are now damage dealers, slowers, stunners, dotters, snarers.  Should I go on?<br>
<br>
Just one of you tell me when the last time you were in one group (to get most of your exp) and you were there just as a tank?  I hear a new phrase out there and thats damage givers not just tanks.  I find I can get into groups easier even outside my own guild either as a tank or a damage giver.<br>
<br>
Always remember<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Tanks especially MT's need what to stay an MT?<br>
<br>
AGGRO and what makes up aggro?  Damage not just the fact you have 7000hp and 1500ac.<br>
<br>
One thing I would like to see is Verant fixing our AA skills....especially dam mitigation so it works properly before PoP comes out instead of dishing out new AA skills that look like an improvement over the old AA skills but are actually the old AA skills that now work and cost you a ton of AA points to get to.<br>
<br>
Fix our freaking epics!  We worked our arses off for them..heck epic means exactly that..the best..top of the heap..its sad when 5 of my weapons are better than my epic.<br>
<br>
Granted I will give you this.  A lot of the other classes are bypassing us that is true but this also happened in the past expansions and we caught up down the road with them when it happened in various ways.<br>
<br>
We are NOT just tanks anymore.  Hell..I don't know what we are anymore.  Hmm...maybe a new hybrid of warriors coming into a brand new world.  We have survived all these years and will survive in the future.  Why?  We are survivors and not quitters.<br>
<br>
Come on warriors.  Remember when you were 50 and damn proud of that bronze armor (full set) or steel armor you finally acquired?  Ok some of you had planar armor but most of us didn't.<br>
<br>
=============================================================<br>
THIS SECTION FOR VERANT!<br>
<br>
One other thing Verant!  You do the same thing every expansion you put out.  You nerf drops in the last expansion starting about 5-6 months from release date, then you nerf exp over and over again then state that getting exp will easier to get in PoP.  Can you say sales coup?  Hmm..wonder how many people will come over to PoP now.<br>
<br>
Lets see we have gone from 20% of one reg exp level in one hour down to 3% of one reg exp level in one hour in a group setting.  Also..you have taken backyard coding and accomplished the following:  When in a group where most of group is between say level 55-59 and you have 2 level 60's that reg exp of one level goes down to 1% per hour.  Why?  Simple the 55-59 get the majority of the reg exp derived from killing the mobs.  Yes..we have even tracked what happened there while in a group setting.<br>
<br>
Here are the results of the testing for you.<br>
<br>
Level 60 = 1% reg exp 1 hour<br>
Level 60 = 1% reg exp 1 hour<br>
Level 59 = 2% reg exp 1 hour<br>
Level 56 = 4% reg exp 1 hour<br>
Level 57 = 4% reg exp 1 hour<br>
Level 58 = 2% reg exp 1 hour<br>
<br>
Yep folks you guessed it.  A escalating % for exp..so the young ones get old quicker but if grouped with them the old ones receive less exp now than before.<br>
<br>
Why you ask?  Simple again.. Thanks to all you freaks out there who wanted to power level their toons up with their level 60 characters and at the same time get uber exp for your level 60 is why.  The level 60's this way were gaining too much AA exp when this happened.<br>
==============================================================<br>
<br>
Lets see what Verant deals out to us first and then if we have to go to them and say hey what about warriors.<br>
<br>
But until then..lets just plain kick arse in the best way we know possible!<br>
<br>
Gigantuous-Warlord<br>
